faa-req-handbook pack — content licence
========================================

This pack is derived from:
    Requirements Engineering Management Handbook (DOT/FAA/AR-08/32)
    U.S. Department of Transportation, Federal Aviation Administration (DOT/FAA)
    June 2009 (Final Report)

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work)  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This Handbook is a Final Report prepared for the Federal Aviation Administration. As a
work of the United States Government, it is NOT subject to copyright protection in the
United States (17 U.S.C. § 105) and is in the public domain: anyone may reproduce,
transform, and redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially, without
permission and without any attribution or share-alike obligation.

DISCLAIMER (paraphrased from the source's NOTICE): the document was disseminated by the
U.S. Department of Transportation in the interest of information exchange. The U.S.
Government assumes no liability for the contents or their use, does not endorse products
or manufacturers, and the document does not constitute FAA certification policy (the
source directs readers to consult their local FAA aircraft certification office as to its
use). This pack inherits that non-endorsement and no-liability posture.

THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL CAVEAT: the Handbook references industry standards that remain the
copyright of their respective publishers and are NOT in the public domain:
    - IEEE Std 1233 and IEEE Std 830-1998        © IEEE
    - RTCA DO-178B, DO-248B, DO-278              © RTCA, Inc.
    - SAE ARP 4754, ARP 4761                     © SAE International
This pack reproduces NONE of those standards. It contains only synthesized, transformed
reference notes that NAME these standards and describe, in original words, how the
Handbook's recommended practices relate to them. No long verbatim passage of the Handbook
itself is reproduced either — the pack synthesizes rather than photocopies (verified by
the repository's check_overlap.py gate).

Attribution to DOT/FAA is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a legal
obligation. The FAA does not endorse this pack or its authors.

NOTE: This licence governs the CONTENT of this pack and is independent of the
repository's MIT licence (which covers tooling only).
